description.narrative: This activity (Rapid Humantiarian Assistance (CHASE OT)) is a component of Yemen: Access, Logistics, Liaison, and Accountability (YALLA) - 2017-20 reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Front Line Delivery' and a budget of £6,002,825. This component benefits Yemen, and works in the following sector(s): Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited, Palladium International Ltd (UK). The start date is 01-08-2017 and the end date is 02-12-2021.
